<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <!-- Metadata goes in the head section and is not visible on the webpage -->
        <meta charset="UTF-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <title>Sample HTML Webpage</title>
        <!-- You can also link external CSS files here -->
        <style>
            body {
                font-family: sans-serif;
                margin: 20px;
            }
            header,
            footer,
            section,
            article,
            nav,
            aside {
                padding: 15px;
                margin-bottom: 10px;
                border: 1px solid #ccc;
            }
            nav ul {
                list-style-type: none;
                padding: 0;
            }
            nav ul li {
                display: inline;
                margin-right: 10px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <!-- The body contains all visible content -->

        <header>
            <h1>Major HTML Elements Example</h1>
            <p>This page demonstrates common HTML tags for structure and content.</p>
        </header>

        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#section1">Section 1</a></li>
                <li><a href="#section2">Section 2</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.example.com">External Link</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>

        <main>
            <section id="section1">
                <h2>Headings and Paragraphs</h2>
                <p>
                    HTML uses headings from <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> for structure. The <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tag defines a
                    paragraph of text. You can use <b>bold text</b> with the <code>&lt;b&gt;</code> tag or <strong>strong text</strong> with the
                    <code>&lt;strong&gt;</code> tag.
                </p>
                <hr />
                <!-- The <hr> tag inserts a horizontal line -->
            </section>

            <section id="section2">
                <h2>Lists and Images</h2>
                <h3>Unordered List (Bulleted)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Item A</li>
                    <li>Item B</li>
                    <li>Item C</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Ordered List (Numbered)</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>First Step</li>
                    <li>Second Step</li>
                    <li>Third Step</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Image Example</h3>
                <p>An image is embedded using the <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tag with <code>src</code> and <code>alt</code> attributes.</p>
                <img src="https://picsum.photos" alt="A cute dog" />
            </section>

            <article>
                <h2>Forms</h2>
                <form action="#" method="post">
                    <label for="name">Name:</label>
                    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" />
                    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
                </form>
            </article>
        </main>

        <footer>
            <p>© 2026 Sample Webpage. All rights reserved.</p>
        </footer>
    </body>
</html>
